705526f-a.text:
Ave. M, at the N.E. corner of East 34th Street, showing the home of John L. Ryder, who was supervisor of the Town of Flatlands 1885-1886, and again in 1894-1895. In 1895 he was elected to the New York Legislature for four years. His estate was bounded on the north by Ave. L, on the south by Ave. M, on the west by Nostrand Ave. and on the east by East 35th Street.
This house was razed sometime between 1922 and 1929.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
